benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/catalog/plan - Retrieve plan for a given subscription and date

covered: Valid Request handling (TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04) - multiple parameter combinations returning 200 with Plan object or appropriate default
Error handling and validation (TC05, TC06, TC07, TC08) - malformed inputs, non-existent subscription, multiple invalid params
Edge cases (TC11, TC12, TC13, TC14) - empty DB, data inconsistency, boundary dates, extra parameters
Security tests (TC17, TC18) - SQL injection and XSS attempt testing
Regression tests (TC19, TC20) - previously fixed issue and backward compatibility
Performance tests (TC15, TC16) - response time under normal and high load
Test coverage of various HTTP status codes for error and success scenarios (200, 400, 404, 401, 503, 409, 422)
gaps: Pagination testing for large datasets not covered
Caching behavior / headers (ETag, Cache-Control) not covered
Rate limiting / throttling tests not covered
Explicit 404 for non-existent resource in the presence of valid inputs not clearly distinguished beyond TC07
No explicit test for mixed valid/invalid extra parameters validation in edge cases beyond basic 14
No dedicated test for very large payloads or unusual but valid payload shapes (beyond query params)
recommendations: Add a dedicated pagination test to validate behavior with large numbers of plans or subscriptions.
Add tests to verify caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) and caching behavior.
Add rate limiting / throttling tests to ensure system tolerates high request rates.
Introduce a test scenario for 403 Forbidden where user is authenticated but lacks permissions (in addition to 401).
Clarify and add a test that explicitly distinguishes 404 when resource truly not found vs 200/204 with empty body for certain parameter combinations.
Include tests for more varied edge conditions around extra/unexpected query parameters, ensuring ignoring behavior across different clients.
